overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure it met all specified acceptance criteria. The review
  identified several critical gaps, leading to a detailed implementation plan.
  The core intent was to enhance the questionnaire's diagnostic capabilities and
  reporting accuracy. The approach involved iteratively implementing each
  identified missing feature, starting with a tiredness severity scale, followed
  by advanced sleep disorder detections like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome. Key decisions included integrating weighted scoring for EDS,
  expanding data export capabilities, and adding crucial pain and chronic
  fatigue screening. The outcome is a significantly more robust and clinically
  relevant sleep questionnaire, providing more accurate assessments and
  actionable insights for users.
